Boston University CS 480/680 Computer Graphics assignments
==========================================================

This package contains programming assignments from Boston University's CS
480/680 Computer Graphics course.

The "assignment1" directory contains a program which draws polygons, tests
whether points are inside or outside the polygon, and partitions a concave
polygon into a union of disjoint convex polygons.

The "assignment2" directory contains an arm and hand simulation with joints
which can be rotated.

The "assignment3" directory contains a simulation of birds and fish, both with
moving parts, which adhere to some flock movement rules.

The "assignment4" directory contains a ray tracer.

